Title: Comparison of Position Estimation Techniques Using Occupancy Grids  
Author: Bernt Schiele and James L. Crowley 
Address: 46 Avenue Felix Viallet 38031 Grenoble Cedex FRANCE  
Affiliation: LIFIA-INPG  
Abstract: This paper addresses the problem of perception and localisation for a mobile robot in an unknown environment. It describes a modelling of the environment based on two certainty grids: one local model and the other one a global model. Localisation of the robot is reduced to finding the best alignment of the local certainty grid onto the global certainty grid. Four localisation procedures to correct the robot position are introduced. First experimental results show the capacity of the method. 
